         <abstract>
            <p>The number S&lt;sub&gt;m&lt;/sub&gt;(α) of solutions of the quadratic equation &lt;tex-math&gt;$x^2_1 + x^2_2 + \cdots + x^2_m = \alpha\quad(x^2_i \neq \pm x^2_j\quad\text{for} i \neq j)$&lt;/tex-math&gt; for given m, with α and x&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; belonging to a finite field, is studied and a recursive method to compute S&lt;sub&gt;m&lt;/sub&gt;(α) is established.</p>
          </abstract>
